title: BWI reports 2.1 million passengers in August
text:
BWI reports 2.1 million passengers in August BWI Airport By Paul W. Gillespie, Staff 
BWI Airport in Linthicum. (By Paul W. Gillespie, Staff) BWI reports 2.1 million passengers in August. 
BWI Thurgood Marshall Airport reported a record-breaking 2.1 million passengers for the month of August on Wednesday. 
The number of August passengers exceeded last year's figure by 5 percent, airport officials said. The airport previously reported having the highest number of July passengers on record this year with 2.2 million. 
International traffic in August increased some 32 percent from 2014. 
Construction is underway for a corridor that will connect the airports D and Concourses. Airport officials say that the project will increase international capacity and provide new passenger services.
